<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870227-0120 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Maxtor Corp.</HL><DD> 02/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MXTRBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><TEXT>   MAXTOR CORP. said it commenced the sale at par of $100 million of 5 3/4% debentures due 2012. The securities are convertible at a rate of $40 of debentures for each common share. Goldman, Sachs andamp; Co. is the sole underwriter. The San Jose, Calif-based maker of disk drives for computer applications, said proceeds will be used for general purposes. In over-the-counter trading yesterday, the company's common closed at $30.875, down 75 cents. </TEXT></DOC>